##Notes for Week 3: 2.2. Consumer Surplus and the Demand Curve

Willingness to pay

Between price and demand curve=consumer surplus

Graphically, it is the area under the demand curve that is above the straight line representing y=price.

[[File:Demand Curve and Consumer Surplus 1.jpg]]

When the price falls, consumer surplus increases.  Likewise, when price increases, the consumer surplus goes away too.

[[File:Demand Curve and Consumer Surplus 2.jpg]]

[[Category:Microecon|Using the Demand Curve]]
